	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001257_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 illegible top left--><!--Hand 02 159 top left--><!--Hand 03 27 top left--><!--Hand 04 64764 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="center"><placeName>Burbank</placeName>,</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">24<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Feby</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice> 1858</p>
<lb/><p>Dear <persName>Lady Belhaven</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I am sorry 
<lb/>that it has been 
<lb/>quite out of my 
<lb/>power to call 
<lb/>and thank you 
<lb/>and <persName>Lady Emma 
<lb/>Campbell</persName> for so 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001257_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>kindly remembering 
<lb/>my African friends 
<lb/>I shall take 
<lb/>the <unclear cert="high">rugs</unclear> to <persName>Sekeletu</persName>
<lb/>and tell him 
<lb/>that they are 
<lb/>presented by two 
<lb/>female chieftains 
<lb/>of my country as 
<lb/>an acknowledgement 
<lb/>for the kindness 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001257_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>he shewed to me 
<lb/>when a solitary 
<lb/>stranger in a strange 
<lb/>land. I had hoped 
<lb/>to have spent 
<lb/>a few days here 
<lb/>but I came from 
<lb/>London yesterday 
<lb/>and go down 
<lb/>to Glasgow tonight - 
<lb/>speak to the 
<lb/>college students 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001257_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/>tomorrow at 3. then 
<lb/>come here on friday 
<lb/>afternoon to say 
<lb/>good bye to my 
<lb/>mother. I beg leave 
<lb/>to say Farewell to 
<lb/>you on paper. and 
<lb/>wish you and 
<lb/><persName>Lord Belhaven</persName>
<lb/>every blessing</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
			
